│ represented by a VPRecipe), isa asserts. Similarly, earlier we test      │
│ isa<VPWidenCastRecipe>(OpR) where OpR =                                  │
│ getOperand(0)->getDefiningRecipe(); OpR can be null if operand 0 is a    │
│ live-in.                                                                 │
│                                                                          │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                  │
│ The root cause is missing null checks before isa<> on pointers returned  │
│ by VPValue::getDefiningRecipe(). LLVM's isa<> on pointer types asserts   │
│ that the pointer is non-null, so we must guard these calls. The code     │
│ already has a helper GetExtendKind that safely handles null recipes, but │
│ it still uses isa<> directly without checking for null, leading to the   │
│ abort in this case where RedPhiOp1R (or OpR) is null for the given IR    │
│ and chosen scalable VF causing partial reduction modeling.               │
│                                                                          │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                               │
│ - File: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlanRecipes.cpp                   │
│ - Edit block around lines 344-356 to add null checks:                    │
│   Change:                                                                │
│     if (isa<VPWidenCastRecipe>(OpR)) {                                   │
│       InputTypeA = Ctx.Types.inferScalarType(OpR->getOperand(0));        │
│       ExtAType = GetExtendKind(OpR);                                     │
│     } else if (isa<VPReductionPHIRecipe>(OpR)) {                         │
│       auto RedPhiOp1R = getOperand(1)->getDefiningRecipe();              │
│       if (isa<VPWidenCastRecipe>(RedPhiOp1R)) {                          │
│         InputTypeA =                                                     │
│ Ctx.Types.inferScalarType(RedPhiOp1R->getOperand(0));                    │
│         ExtAType = GetExtendKind(RedPhiOp1R);                            │
│       } else if (auto Widen = dyn_cast<VPWidenRecipe>(RedPhiOp1R))       │
│         HandleWiden(Widen);                                              │
│     } else if (auto Widen = dyn_cast<VPWidenRecipe>(OpR)) {              │
│       HandleWiden(Widen);                                                │
│     } else if (auto Reduction = dyn_cast<VPPartialReductionRecipe>(OpR)) │
│ {                                                                        │
│       return Reduction->computeCost(VF, Ctx);                            │
│     }                                                                    │
│   To:                                                                    │
│     if (OpR && isa<VPWidenCastRecipe>(OpR)) {                            │
│       InputTypeA = Ctx.Types.inferScalarType(OpR->getOperand(0));        │
│       ExtAType = GetExtendKind(OpR);                                     │
│     } else if (OpR && isa<VPReductionPHIRecipe>(OpR)) {                  │
│       if (auto RedPhiOp1R = getOperand(1)->getDefiningRecipe()) {        │
│         if (isa<VPWidenCastRecipe>(RedPhiOp1R)) {                        │
│           InputTypeA =                                                   │
│ Ctx.Types.inferScalarType(RedPhiOp1R->getOperand(0));                    │
│           ExtAType = GetExtendKind(RedPhiOp1R);                          │
│         } else if (auto Widen = dyn_cast<VPWidenRecipe>(RedPhiOp1R))     │
│           HandleWiden(Widen);                                            │
│       }                                                                  │
│     } else if (auto Widen = dyn_cast<VPWidenRecipe>(OpR)) {              │
│       HandleWiden(Widen);                                                │
│     } else if (auto Reduction = dyn_cast<VPPartialReductionRecipe>(OpR)) │
│ {                                                                        │
│       return Reduction->computeCost(VF, Ctx);                            │
│     }                                                                    │
│                                                                          │
│ These changes ensure that we never call isa<> on a nullptr and keep      │
│ existing behavior otherwise.                                             │
│                                                                          │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                           │
│ By guarding isa<> checks with non-null tests for recipes returned by     │
│ getDefiningRecipe(), we prevent the assertion failure while preserving   │
│ the intended cost modeling logic. This fix should eliminate the abort    │
│ for the provided reproducer and similar cases where operands are         │
│ live-ins or otherwise lack defining recipes.                             │
