│ The patch adds necessary null-pointer guards in                          │
│ VPPartialReductionRecipe::computeCost to prevent calling isa<> on a null │
│ pointer returned by VPValue::getDefiningRecipe(), which caused the       │
│ original SIGABRT in the reproducer. Specifically:                        │
│                                                                          │
│ - Guard isa<VPWidenCastRecipe>(OpR) with OpR non-null.                   │
│ - Guard isa<VPReductionPHIRecipe>(OpR) with OpR non-null and only        │
│ inspect RedPhiOp1R if getDefiningRecipe() returns non-null.              │
│ - Preserve existing behavior for other dyn_cast branches.                │
│                                                                          │
│ This fix addresses the root cause without altering cost modeling logic   │
│ beyond avoiding the crash.                                               │
│                                                                          │
│ Patch summary:                                                           │
│ - File: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlanRecipes.cpp                   │
│ - Changes:                                                               │
│   - Replace direct isa<> calls with checks that OpR and RedPhiOp1R are   │
│ non-null before casting.                                                 │
│                                                                          │
│ The reproducer no longer triggers the Casting.h assertion.               │
