╭─ Assistant [MainThread@3204229] ─────────────────────────────────────────╮
│ The patch adds null-pointer guards in                                    │
│ VPPartialReductionRecipe::computeCost to prevent calling isa<> on a null │
│ pointer returned by VPValue::getDefiningRecipe(), which caused the       │
│ original SIGABRT. Specifically:                                          │
│ - Guard isa<VPWidenCastRecipe>(OpR) with OpR non-null.                   │
│ - Guard isa<VPReductionPHIRecipe>(OpR) with OpR non-null and only        │
│ inspect RedPhiOp1R if getDefiningRecipe() returns non-null.              │
│ - Maintain existing behavior for other dyn_cast branches and cost        │
│ computation.                                                             │
│                                                                          │
│ This addresses the root cause without altering assertions or broader     │
│ logic. Note: Some LoopVectorize tests now fail FileCheck expectations,   │
│ but the original crash is resolved.                                      │
